OL,6,FMr Dodman added: "Last year followed
OL,7,Fan unprecedented period for the energy
OL,8,Fsector, which saw prices hit at an all-
OL,9,Ftime high, and a number of suppliers
OL,10,Fleave the market.
OL,12,F"In this context, it's understandable
OL,13,Fwhy we saw people turn to the Energy
OL,14,FOmbudsman to make sure they were being
OL,15,Ftreated fairly.
OL,17,F"As the market has stabilised
OL,18,Fsomewhat, we have seen the number of
OL,19,Fcomplaints reduce this year, but they
OL,20,Fremain higher than they were before
OL,21,Fthe crisis.
